My commentary in the beginning says everything about what I think about this. Lol. Do not try this or do this. It did polish the tank properly and did shine it up right. BUT!!!!! Full story. I was training a crew in Minnesota as part of my training program and the one guy told me he polished the bottoms of tanks different. Now I’m a firm believer on to each their own. But as a business I watch this and see it as a workers comp claim waiting to happen. It’s like looking down the barrel of a bazooka. I preach and teach safe procedures as often as possible. Many things about metal polishing you have to take risks because things just get in the way. No I don’t use a handle. No we don’t have guards. No I don’t wear gloves. Some of those safe things I find out me in more danger and risk. With gloves I can’t feel what’s going on and I lose dexterity. But with all that said…. There isn’t a wrong way to polish if it’s shining the way you want it to. Watch and enjoy.

Apparently the last video arose a lot of controversy. In no way shape or form am I telling anyone they should polish like that. In fact if you read the post I said to not do that. Polishing like that is very dangerous. Not only is it dangerous but polishing can be life threatening even when done properly. So many things can go wrong really fast. Especially at 6,000 rpm. Thanks for reading and be safe.
